- The Selling Module helps a company manage its entire sales process, from getting a new lead to collecting payment after selling a product or service.

Main Goal : To track how your product/service moves from interest â†’ quotation â†’ order â†’ delivery â†’ payment.
Used By : Sales Team, Sales Managers, and sometimes Accountants.
Connected Modules :
   ğŸ”— CRM (for leads & opportunities)
   ğŸ“¦ Stock (for delivery)
   ğŸ’° Accounts (for invoices & payments)
   ğŸ­ Buying (for linked supplier sales, if any)
   
   
   
ğŸ§  Why Selling Module is Important

|   **Reason**               | ğŸ’¬ **Meaning (Simple)**                                                                                 |
| ---------------------------| ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1ï¸âƒ£ Centralized Control     | You can track every step of the sales process in one place.                                             |
| 2ï¸âƒ£ Improves Accuracy       | No need to manage quotations, invoices, or delivery notes separately. ERPNext links them automatically. |
| 3ï¸âƒ£ Saves Time              | One click converts a **Quotation â†’ Sales Order â†’ Delivery Note â†’ Invoice**.                             |
| 4ï¸âƒ£ Customer Insights       | You can see which customers buy often, what they buy, and when.                                         |
| 5ï¸âƒ£ Stock & Accounting Sync | Sales automatically affect stock and accounts (e.g., reduces stock, increases revenue).                 |



ğŸ§­ Simple Example (Real-World View)	
Letâ€™s say you sell Laptops ğŸ–¥ï¸

| Step | What Happens                       | ERPNext Document             |
| ---- | ---------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| 1ï¸âƒ£  | You get a new interested person    | **Lead**                     |
| 2ï¸âƒ£  | You qualify it as a potential sale | **Opportunity**              |
| 3ï¸âƒ£  | You send them a price offer        | **Quotation**                |
