- If the checkbox is checked, the user can modify it to â‚¹95 or â‚¹110 as needed.

----------

2. Validate Selling Price Against Purchase/Valuation
- This option ensures that the selling price (Rate in transactions like Sales Order, Sales Invoice, etc.) is not lower than your purchase or valuation rate.

----------

3.Calculate Product Bundle Price (Child Item Rates)
- This setting decides how ERPNext calculates the total price of a Product Bundle in your selling transactions (Quotation, Sales Order, Sales Invoice, etc.).

A Product Bundle = A main (parent) item + multiple child items.
Example:
ğŸ‘‰ â€œDesktop Computer Setâ€ = CPU, Monitor, Keyboard, Mouse

Parent Item: Desktop Computer Set
Child Items: CPU, Monitor, Keyboard, Mouse


so, When This Checkbox is Unchecked (Default)
The price of the bundle is taken from the parent itemâ€™s price (the Product Bundle item itself).

| Item                 | Type   | Rate    | Used For Calculation |
| -------------------- | ------ | ------- | -------------------- |
| Desktop Computer Set | Parent | â‚¹50,000 | âœ… Taken              |
| CPU                  | Child  | â‚¹20,000 | âŒ Ignored            |
| Monitor              | Child  | â‚¹15,000 | âŒ Ignored            |
| Keyboard             | Child  | â‚¹5,000  | âŒ Ignored            |
| Mouse                | Child  | â‚¹2,000  | âŒ Ignored            |

Total = â‚¹50,000 (from parent)

âš™ï¸ When This Checkbox is Checked (Enabled)
- ERPNext calculates the price of the Product Bundle based on the total of all child item rates instead of the parent itemâ€™s rate.

| Item                 | Type   | Rate    | Used For Calculation |
| -------------------- | ------ | ------- | -------------------- |
| Desktop Computer Set | Parent | â‚¹0      | âŒ Ignored            |
| CPU                  | Child  | â‚¹20,000 | âœ… Included           |
| Monitor              | Child  | â‚¹15,000 | âœ… Included           |
| Keyboard             | Child  | â‚¹5,000  | âœ… Included           |
| Mouse                | Child  | â‚¹2,000  | âœ… Included           |

Total = â‚¹42,000 (sum of child items)

----------

4. Allow Negative Rates for Items
- This setting controls whether you can enter a negative rate (i.e., a rate < 0) in sales transactions (like Sales Order, Sales Invoice, Delivery Note, etc.).

- ERPNext normally doesnâ€™t allow negative rates, because that would mean youâ€™re selling an item and paying the customer â€” which is usually a mistake.
- But in some special use cases, itâ€™s intentionally required.

ex.
| Item      | Qty | Rate | Explanation                                           |
| --------- | --- | ---- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Product A | 1   | 500  | Normal sale                                           |
| Product A | 1   | -500 | Negative rate â€” e.g., return, discount, or adjustment |

âš™ï¸ When Checkbox is Unchecked (Default)
- Negative rate is not allowed.
- If you try to enter one, ERPNext throws validation like: â€œRate cannot be negative for item X.â€


âš™ï¸ When Checkbox is Checked (Enabled)
- System allows you to enter negative rates freely.
- Mostly used for:
   Credit adjustments
   Promotional discounts (item-wise instead of total)
   Return transactions
   Reverse entries
   
   
