Other :

1. Donâ€™t Reserve Sales Order Qty on Sales Returnâ€ in ERPNext

ğŸ§© Example
Scenario:
- You have a Sales Order for 10 units.
- You delivered 10 units (Sales Order fully delivered).
- Customer returns 2 units (Sales Return created).

Now, depending on the checkbox:

| Checkbox Status | Effect on Sales Order       | Explanation                                                                                      |
| --------------- | --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| âŒ **Unchecked** | Reserved qty increases by 2 | ERPNext assumes you might re-deliver those 2 units, so it â€œreopensâ€ part of the Sales Order.     |
| âœ… **Checked**   | No change in reserved qty   | ERPNext treats the return as a final reversal â€” it wonâ€™t plan to re-deliver those 2 items again. |



ğŸ§  When to Check This Option

Check this if:
- You donâ€™t want to re-open or re-reserve Sales Orders when items are returned.
- Your business treats returns as final and manages replacements as new orders.

Leave it unchecked if:
- You want to allow re-delivery from the same Sales Order after a return (common in replacement workflows).





